image.altText: A woman walks out of the Darwin Local Court

props.synopsis: The disclosure of information resulted in a number of outlets, including the Australian, the ABC and the NT Independent, publishing articles containing information that had not yet been made public.

title.children: Former NT courts media liaison pleads guilty to providing restricted information to journalists

image.altText: A lone shopper reaches for an item on an otherwise bare set of shelves in a supermarket's fresh produce section.

props.synopsis: The Northern Territory's major highway has reopened to the general public, bringing fresh fruit and vegetables back to Top End supermarket shelves after days of shortages.

title.children: Fresh produce returns to NT supermarket shelves as Stuart Highway reopens after flooding

image.altText: Scott Morrison high vis

props.synopsis: The former prime minister Scott Morrison was not shy in his dealings with foreign leaders, adversaries or the press gallery. But he has ended his political career quietly, with a simple post on Facebook.

title.children: 'Miracle' man Scott Morrison calls time on political career, new job beckons in US

image.altText: Jim Chalmers in the foreground in focus, with Anthony Albanese in the background out of focus, from the right hand side

props.synopsis: Ahead of Labor's cost-of-living caucus, the crosshairs have again settled on the stage 3 tax cuts that are months away from handing more than $20 billion a year from the government back to (mainly) higher income earners.

title.children: The stage 3 tax cuts are only months away, but here's what could change in the meantime

image.altText: Flood water flows over the top of a bridge

props.synopsis: Road access to the Kimberley towns of Halls Creek, Kununurra and Wyndham has been cut off by flooding across two major highways, although residents are well stocked and prepared for wet season challenges.

title.children: Empty shelves and travel delays as flooding leaves East Kimberley communities cut off

image.altText: Woman wearing a black top smiling for a portrait.

props.synopsis: Because genetic testing found Meg Herrmann had an increased risk of breast cancer, life insurers can legally use that information to discriminate against her.

title.children: It’s a simple test that can save lives, but those who take it can face a legal form of financial discrimination

image.altText: Sophie holds a football and pouts at the camera.

props.synopsis: At just 13 years old, Sophie had a bad experience on the footy field, but is speaking out because she's proud of her Aboriginal heritage. It's a story experts say is too common.

title.children: Sophie was called a racist name playing footy – she wants her story to be heard

image.altText: Tasmanian Police Officer Paul Reynolds at a press conference.

props.synopsis: A Tasmanian police officer who died by suicide while under investigation is described as a "charismatic" groomer in a review that details three decades of offending.

title.children: Former police officer used positions of authority to abuse children for three decades, report finds

image.altText: Aryna Sabalenka, in a red top and sport skirt, hits a double-handed backhand, during a night match

props.synopsis: Defending Australian Open women's champion Aryna Sabalenka is on Rod Laver Arena against Barbora Krejcikova, after Novak Djokovic beat Taylor Fritz in four sets. Follow live.

title.children: Defending champion takes centrestage after Novak Djokovic storms into 11th semifinal at Melbourne Park

image.altText: ABC Managing Director David Anderson

props.synopsis: The ABC board passes a unanimous vote of confidence in the broadcaster's managing director David Anderson after union members called on Mr Anderson to take immediate action to win back the confidence of staff.

title.children: ABC board passes unanimous vote of confidence in managing director David Anderson

image.altText: optus 'yes' sign on glass fronted office block

props.synopsis: Optus admits more than 2,500 people tried and failed to call triple-0 from their mobiles during last November's network outage, after previously telling a Senate inquiry just 228 people were affected.

title.children: Optus reveals 10 times more people affected by triple-0 failures than previously known

image.altText: A map showing a swirling weather system off the coast of north Queensland.

props.synopsis: The system is now forecast to cross the coast late on Thursday between Cardwell and Airlie Beach.

image.altText: Map showing rainfall totals over Australia

props.synopsis: The slow-moving system is still gathering moisture over the Coral Sea, meaning it will bring rain to a broad area once it crosses over land.

image.altText: Former prison guard awaits sentencing outside court

props.synopsis: Former prison guard Liana Braithwaite has been sentenced to 80 hours of community service for engaging in intimate relations on multiple times with a high-ranking member of the Nomads outlaw motorcycle gang in her care.

title.children: Magistrate spares former guard jail time for kissing Nomads bikie boss in high security

image.altText: A row of blue and white flowers and photographs are laid out above a Victoria Police marble floor.

props.synopsis: Cris Large will spend at least one year in jail for failing to ensure his company operated safely before a crash that killed four police officers on Melbourne's Eastern Freeway.

title.children: Trucking boss jailed for 2020 crash that killed four Victorian police officers

image.altText: Israeli soldiers operate in the Gaza Strip amid the ongoing conflict between Israel and Hamas.

image.altText: Coco Gauff screams out as she celebrates a win at the 2024 Australian Open.

image.altText: Glenn Maxwell

props.synopsis: Glenn Maxwell has resumed training after ending up in an Adelaide hospital following a concert involving cult band Six & Out.

image.altText: A man walks off after a coin toss before a cricket match

image.altText: A player fends off an opponent during a rugby league match

image.altText: Coc Gauff pumps her left fist at the 2024 Australian Open.

image.altText: A man smiling at the camera while screwing something into a wall.

props.synopsis: A woman is remembering her brother as a "hero", saying he saved the lives of three children who were caught in a rip at Mary Ellis Beach, south-west of Port Lincoln on Friday. She has launched a fundraiser to support his wife and four children.

image.altText: A woman sitting in a car.

props.synopsis: A Perth woman thought she was calling her insurer to make a claim, but found herself caught up in a scheme that whisked her car away and cost more than $6,000 to undo.

image.altText: Woman with a striped jumper works on a laptop while holding a baby at a desk in her home.

props.synopsis: Mental load is burden created by the unseen, exhausting unpaid labour associated with juggling work, family and running a household. But there are ways to ease the pressure.

props.synopsis: The Australian government has imposed sanctions against Russian man Aleksandr Ermakov over his role in the Medibank Private data breach.

title.children: Who is Aleksandr Ermakov, the man linked to the Medibank Private cyber attack?

image.altText: Aleksandr Ermakov sitting in a chair in what appears to be a high-end bottle shop
